{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext\/pushThreadDefault()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Acquires "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(such as most ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html"},{"type":"text","text":"-based I\/O) which are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"started in this thread to run under ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"changes the context returned by [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not the one returned by [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.default"},{"text":"], so it does not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"affect the context used by functions like [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext\/MainContextProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Normally you would call this function shortly after creating a new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"thread, passing it a [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] which will be run by a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] in that thread, to set a new default context for all"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"async operations in that thread. In this case you may not need to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ever call [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], assuming you want","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the new [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] to be the default for the whole lifecycle"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the thread.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t have control over how the new thread was created (e.g.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the new thread isn’t newly created, or if the thread life"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cycle is managed by a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","type":"reference"},{"text":"), it is always suggested to wrap","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the logic that needs to use the new [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] inside a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] \/"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"] pair, otherwise threads that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are re-used will end up never explicitly releasing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"] reference they hold."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In some cases you may want to schedule a single operation in a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-default context, or temporarily use a non-default context in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the main thread. In that case, you can wrap the call to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"asynchronous operation inside a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] \/"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] pair, but it is up to you to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ensure that no other asynchronous operations accidentally get"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"started while the non-default context is active."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Beware that libraries that predate this function may not correctly","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"handle being used from a thread with a thread-default context. For example,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"see ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_file_supports_thread_contexts()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext\/pushthreaddefault()"]}],"metadata":{"title":"pushThreadDefault()","externalID":"s:4GLib19MainContextProtocolPAAE17pushThreadDefaultyyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib11MainContextC","extendedModule":"GLib","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}]},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPool":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct represents a thread pool.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool","title":"ThreadPool","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","title":"MainContext","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":